        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 3:56PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Moulton, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Decatur, Trinity, Chalybeate Springs, Hillsboro, Moulton, Caddo,
Basham, and Wren.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
